5000|$|Central pontine myelinolysis is a {{demyelination}} {{disease that}} causes difficulty with sense of balance, walking, sense of touch, swallowing and speaking. In a clinical setting, {{it is often}} associated with transplant or rapid correction of blood sodium. Undiagnosed, it can lead to death or <b>locked-in</b> <b>syndrome.</b>|$|E
