5000|$|<b>Locked-in</b> <b>syndrome</b> is a {{condition}} in which a patient is aware and awake, but cannot move or communicate due to complete paralysis of the body. Voluntary control of eye movements or blinking may be spared, permitting the detection of conscious awareness and enabling the establishment of functional communication.|$|E
50|$|The Diving Bell and the Butterfly (original French title: Le Scaphandre et le Papillon) is {{a memoir}} by {{journalist}} Jean-Dominique Bauby. It describes what {{his life is}} like after suffering a massive stroke that left him with <b>locked-in</b> <b>syndrome.</b> It also details what his life was like before the stroke.|$|E
